article.headline: E. Kentucky 61, Youngstown St. 50
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Darnell Dialls scored 17 points to lead Eastern Kentucky to a 61-50 win over Youngstown State on Saturday. The Colonels (3-4) never trailed and snapped a four-game losing streak. The Penguins fell to 3-3. Dialls scored 12 in the first half on 6-of-9 shooting from the floor and led four Eastern players in double figures. Mike Rose followed Dialls with 12 points and Adam Leonard and Jamaal Douglas added 10 points each. The Colonels held a 39-34 lead with 14 minutes left and went on a 10-2 run to push the margin to 52-38. Jack Liles didn't score in the first half, but led the Penguins with 18 points and 10 rebounds. Liles scored 10 of Youngtown State's first 13 points of the second half that trimmed a 29-19 halftime deficit to 38-32 with 15:34 remaining. John Barber followed Liles with 11 points.
